<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1846,2027]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,410]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">
Neither morphological nor molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[667,909,1846,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[779,839,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[922,1131,1846,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1002,1062,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) support this as a distinct section. Two distinct pollen 
<typeStatus box="[501,568,1885,1911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">types</typeStatus>
, perforate and foveolate, were observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Vvedensky (1932: 269)" authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityPageNumber="269" authorityYear="1932" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graminifolia">
<emphasis box="[1101,1291,1885,1910]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G. graminifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vvedensky, A. I." pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="269" refId="ref11014" refString="Vvedensky, A. I. (1932) p. 261 &amp; p. 269, in: Fedtschenko, B. A. (ed.) Flora Turkemenii vol. 1. Turkmenskoe Gosudarstvennoe Izd., Ashkhabad." type="book chapter" year="1932">Vvedensky (1932: 269)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1946" box="[349,463,1924,1949]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vegeta">
<emphasis box="[349,463,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G. vegeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively, both included in this section (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." box="[990,1239,1924,1950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Morphological and ontogenetic characters were mentioned as synapomorphies of 
<emphasis box="[949,978,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1049,1218,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Graminifoliae</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1375,1436,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, but these are also shared with other sections, such as 
<emphasis box="[885,913,2001,2026]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="Levichev" authorityName="Levichev" authorityYear="1814" box="[984,1347,2001,2027]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis box="[984,1228,2001,2026]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Platyspermum sensu</emphasis>
Levichev
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1407,1435,2001,2026]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[214,351,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Incrustatae</emphasis>
. Anatomical characters also do not support the monophyly of 
<emphasis box="[1117,1146,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1218,1389,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Graminifoliae</emphasis>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1946" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vegeta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. vegeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the only included species in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Ingrouille, M. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[611,867,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="155 - 177" refId="ref11602" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Ingrouille, M. J, Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2010 d) The systematic importance of anatomical data in Gagea (Liliaceae) from Flora Iranica area. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 164: 155 - 177." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[697,760,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2010d)
</bibRefCitation>
grouped with 
<emphasis box="[1052,1081,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sections 
<emphasis box="[1200,1309,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Minimae</emphasis>
(Pascher) Davlianidze and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wolfe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[356,435,229,254]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[356,435,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Gagea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In analyses of nrITS and plastid sequences (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[986,1204,229,255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1070,1131,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
), the only included species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1946" box="[250,362,268,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vegeta">
<emphasis box="[250,362,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. vegeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is embedded in clade C, the species of which form an enlarged 
<emphasis box="[1116,1145,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1212,1381,268,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1381,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[249,507,306,332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[359,420,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
included three species of 
<emphasis box="[821,849,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[920,1088,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Graminifoliae</emphasis>
in their analyses, and all fall into the clade containing other members of 
<emphasis box="[671,700,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[770,940,345,370]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[770,940,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as used here. All available data therefore indicate that this section should be merged with an expanded 
<emphasis box="[872,900,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[968,1137,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1137,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
